Computes option price via Black-Scholes-Merton formula.

Source: R/bsm.R
bsmprice.Rd

Black-Scholes-Merton formula implementation, pricing european options.

Usage

bsmprice(type, spot, strike, time, rate, yield, sigma)

Arguments

type

'call' for call option, any other value for put.

spot

current stock price.

strike

the strike price.

time

time to option expiration in years.

rate

the risk-free interest rate.

yield

the dividends that are expected to be paid.

sigma

volatility of the stock price.

Value

Vector with price of european options on stocks, according to Black-Scholes-Merton model.

Recycle rule

These arguments handle the recycle rule so vectors can be provided and once those vectors differs in length the recycle rule is applied.

Examples

bsmprice(c("call", "put"), c(50, 49, 48, 47), 45, 0.25, 0.13, 0.01, 0.2)
#> [1] 6.5031266 0.2854164 4.7405597 0.6079959
